column13: reported significance as indicated by eye-catcher ("stars"): 1 means p-value smaller than 0.01, 5 means p-value smaller than 0.05 and so on. If no significance reported, type in 0. Use German decimal seperator, i.e. "," instead of "."
column14: significance thresholds in the paper by which results are distinguished; e.g. if there are three thresholds <0.01, <0.05, <0.1, then S(10), S(5) and S(1) should contain 1 and S(0.1) and S(15) should contain zero
column19: coder: HK for Henning Kosmalla and PP for Peter Pütz
